Notes: Some doubt exists as to the inclusion of H.H. Fletcher for the DFC. The Australian War Memorial Nominal Role for WW1 notes a H.B. Fletcher as winner of the DFC with enlistment date 14th Jan 1915 prior to the formation of the Club. The Clubs Enlistment Book shows a H.H. Fletcher who enlisted 31st May 1915 in the 6th Field Ambulance. It is not known if H.B. Fletcher had any connection with the Club.
Died of wounds at Hebuterne, France. 9th April 1918, aged 20 years.
Also in loving memory of Cecil Harcourt Fallick, late A.I.F., died 6th April 1924
In memory of Roy Dunsmore Gilfillan who died on transport at sea, 23rd June 1915.
19 [?] Battalion, died at Malta 15 August 1915 from wounds received in the charge of the 1st Brigade, Lone Pine, Gallipoli. Aged 22 years.
Killed in action at Bullecourt 3rd May 1917. Aged 25 years.
Died 8th June 1917 of wounds received at Messines. Aged 28 years.
